  "text": "Up to now, the only component of the gram-positive bacterial cell wall whose action on the induction of NO synthase was well characterized was LTA. We show that a second component of gram-positive bacteria, RGPs, is able to induce NO synthase activity. In contrast, peptidoglycan G, another cell wall component, is not effective as a single component but only increases the effects of LTA [CITATION_1] .",
